A 56-year-old man, Mr Ahunwan Francis Enogieru, has been arraigned before an Ogbeson Magistrate Court in Benin for allegedly presenting himself as a legal practitioner with intent to defraud unsuspecting members of the public In the police charge sheet signed by Mr N.A.Ukpebor for F.B Oboezele of Zone 5 Headquarters, Nigeria Police Benin, Enogieru was brought before the Court on a twelve count charge of impersonation, unlawful possession of property belonging to one Williams Erewele among others. Enogieru was alleged to have between 2015 and February 2020, prepared several deeds of transfer/conveyance without authority thereby committing an offence punishable under Section 484 of the Criminal Code Cap 48 Vol.11 Laws of the defunct Bendel State of Nigeria 1996 as applicable to Edo State He was also accused of preparing letter headed papers with the caption “M.I.Ahunwan, Esq, M.I.Ahunwan & Co, Barrister and Solicitor, No 170 Agbor Road, Benin- City without authority thereby committing an offence under Section 484 of the Criminal Code Cap 48 Vol.11 Laws of the defunct Bendel State of Nigeria 1976 as applicable to Edo State. He was alleged to have used the letter headed papers to prepare, a “Notice to pay arrears of rent within 30days ” to Ikponmwosa Agboneni and other tenants in Plot 170 Benin – Agbor road punishable under section 484 of the Criminal Code Cap 48 Vol.11 of the laws of the defunct Bendel state as applicable to Edo State. Mr Enogieru was alleged to have unlawfully converted the sum of N1,170,000.00 being rent paid by one Joshua Edofor to his use, property belonging to one Williams Arewele, thereby committing an offence punishable under section 390 (9) of the Criminal Code Cap 48 Vol. 11 Laws of the defunct Bendel State of Nigeria as applicable to Edo State. He however pleaded not guilty to the charges as read to him. Meanwhile, Chief Magistrate T. Omoruyi has adjourned a further hearing of the case to 3, May 2022.